{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, our results reinforce that the public perceives physicians as more appropriate sources of medical information than AI-based tools.",
    "This outcome is in line with earlier findings on algorithm aversion (7), particularly within the medical domain (e.g., (11)).",
    "Conversely, the use of AI may have been perceived as \"dehumanizing\" (15), a sentiment highlighted by the lower empathy scores for AI-labelled advice in both of our studies.",
    "A further explanation for the observed resistance to AI-generated medical advice might be the phenomenon of \"uniqueness neglect\", wherein users believe AI may not adequately consider their individual characteristics.",
    "Consequently, explaining that even AI-generated advice also processes and considers personal information provided by the individuals themselves could potentially increase acceptance (16)."
  ]
}